        h2 AND (∧) Conjunction Operator
        br

        h3 Definitions
        blockquote
          p Let p and q be propositions. The conjunction of p and q, denoted by p ∧ q, is the proposition “p and q.” The conjunction p ∧ q is true when both p and q are true and is false otherwise.
        br

        h3 Example
        h4 Question:
        p Find the conjunction of the propositions p ∧ q where …
        br
        blockquote
          p p : “Rebecca’s PC has more than 16 GB free hard disk space”
          p q : “The processor in Rebecca’s PC runs faster than 1 GHz.”
        br
        h4 Answer:
        p The conjunction of these propositions, p ∧ q, is the proposition.
        br
        blockquote
          p Rebecca’s PC has more than 16 GB free hard disk space, and the processor in Rebecca’s PC runs faster than 1 GHz.
        br
        p For this conjunction to be true, both conditions given must be true. It is false, when one or both of these conditions are false.
        br

